pulses.name: 20250120 Most Active Threat Indicators
pulses.description:
20 Jan 2025 : Most Active Threat Indicators
#Cybersecurity #Cyberattack #RCE #Botnet #IOC

Top 3 Source Countries:

- China (CN) - China is a leading source of cyber activities, with numerous instances of remote code execution attacks, particularly targeting Dasan GPON devices and D-Link vulnerabilities.
- United States (US) - The US shows a high frequency of attacks, including Back Orifice traffic and various instances of exploitation through the ZGrab scanner.
- India (IN) - India is notable for multiple attacks involving NETGEAR DGN1000 vulnerabilities and DZS GPON remote code execution, indicating a focus on exploiting known weaknesses.

https://www.linkedin.com/posts/starlightintel_cybersecurity-cyberattack-rce-activity-7287144968912097280-UHce?utm_source=share&utm_medium=member_desktop

pulses.name: 20250114 Most Active Threat Indicators
pulses.description:
14 Jan 2025 : Most Active Threat Indicators
#Cybersecurity #Cyberattack #RCE #Botnet #IOC

Top 3 Source Countries:

- United States (US) - The US is a major source of cyber activities, with numerous instances of attacks including Apache HTTP Server vulnerabilities, Back Orifice traffic, and various scanning activities.
- China (CN) - China shows a high frequency of attacks, particularly involving command injections and vulnerabilities in D-Link devices and Apache HTTP servers.
- India (IN) - India is notable for multiple attacks targeting GPON routers and D-Link devices, often exploiting command injection vulnerabilities.
